Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Original task: ship the scheduling MVP. Round 1 review fixes were already
applied (live-prompt re-fetch, atomic runCount, scheduler options, WS task
payload). This commit closes round 2 and the approval-with-comments items.

Round-2 fixes:

1) maxConcurrent now counts in-flight executions, not unique task IDs.
   - SchedulerService.running changed from Set<string> to Map<taskId, count>.
   - Concurrency gate sums the values; overlap check uses count > 0.
   - Increment on start, decrement in finally; entry deleted at zero.
   - Fixes a regression where overlapPolicy='allow' on a single task
     could exceed the global cap.

2) Tighter Zod validation on /api/schedules (POST + PATCH):
   - name: regex /^[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9 _-]*$/, max 100.
   - timezone: max 64 chars (was unbounded).
   - maxRetries: max 5 (was 10).
   - timeoutSec: max 7200 (was 86400).
   - sessionId: max 128.
   - Duplicate name → 409 Conflict on both create and update
     (was 500 from raw SQLite UNIQUE constraint).

3) SchedulesTab UI polish to match the spec:
   - Timezone is now a <select> populated from
     Intl.supportedValuesOf('timeZone'), with a curated fallback list.
   - New "Max retries (0–5)" input alongside the timeout field.
   - Inline cron + name validation: red border + helper text for invalid
     input, and the submit button is disabled until the form is valid.
   - timeoutSec input is clamped client-side to 0..7200 to match server.

Approval-with-comments fixes:

4) Removed `protect: true` from the croner job options. Croner's overrun
   protection was suppressing every cron-fired overlap at the engine
   layer, silently overriding overlapPolicy='allow' (and weakening
   'queue'). All overlap decisions now flow through executeTask() — the
   single source of truth for policy. Added a regression test that fires
   actual cron callbacks via croner's .trigger() to prove cron-fired
   overlaps with 'allow' run concurrently.

5) WS schedule_triggered now carries triggerType ('cron' | 'manual'), so
   the live-running execution row shows the correct badge for manual
   triggers without waiting for a refresh. ServerMessage type updated;
   web handler reads it with a fallback to 'cron' for backward compat.

6) Service-layer fail-fast validation in createTask/updateTask:
   - Cron expressions are constructed (paused) to verify they parse.
   - Timezone strings are validated via Intl.DateTimeFormat.
   - Both throw before persisting, so non-REST callers (CLI seeds, future
     automation, internal tests) cannot create unmountable rows that
     would silently never fire.
   - REST handlers now map "Invalid cron expression" / "Invalid timezone"
     to HTTP 400 (was leaking as 500 for invalid timezone since Zod only
     enforces length, not IANA validity).
   - UI: maxRetries field labelled "(reserved)" with helper note that it
     is not yet wired into execution semantics — explicit MVP scope.
   - 4 new tests: invalid cron + invalid timezone at the service layer,
     "row stays intact on rejected update", and the API contract test
     asserting invalid timezone returns 400 (not 500).
   - GET /api/schedules/:id/executions now returns 404 for unknown ids
     (previously masked as an empty 200 list, hiding client typos). New
     test locks in this contract.
   - SchedulerService constructor validates the configured
     `scheduling.defaultTimezone` and falls back to "UTC" with a warning
     log if invalid (no more silent mount-failure cascades from a typo'd
     IANA name in gateway config).
   - Web liveTriggers refactored from Set<taskId> to
     Map<taskId, Set<executionId>> so the "running" badge stays lit
     while overlapPolicy='allow' has multiple concurrent executions in
     flight — the badge only clears when the LAST in-flight run finishes.
   - 111/111 tests pass; web typecheck clean.

7) New "One-shot run at" datetime-local input on the create form. When set,
   the gateway runs the task once at that instant and auto-pauses (the
   scheduler already supported runAt — only the UI was missing). Hidden
   on edit since runAt is create-only on the server. Client-side guard
   rejects past timestamps before submit, and the server now enforces the
   same future-only contract via Zod refine (returns 400 on past runAt;
   new test locks it in). 112/112 tests pass.

8) Form UX polish: secondary tuning knobs (timezone, overlap policy,
   max retries, timeout, one-shot runAt) now live inside a collapsible
   <details>"Advanced" panel so the common "name + cron + prompt + agent
   mode" path stays uncluttered. Native disclosure widget keeps it
   keyboard- and screen-reader-accessible without extra state.

Tests:
- 8 new gateway tests covering name regex (3), maxRetries cap, timeoutSec
  cap, timezone length cap, 409 on duplicate, and the in-flight counting
  regression. 104/104 gateway tests pass.
- Web typecheck clean.
- End-to-end smoke via the dev proxy confirmed validation responses,
  the 409 conflict path, and one-shot runAt scheduling.

